race.comment: SMART AND MIGHTY (17) was also an acceptor at Mornington on Friday, but you'd think they'd like to run here on the home track if he sneaks a run. Nosed out as a short-priced favourite first-up and then well-held last time out when a noted drifter. Extra distance here looks suitable at this stage of the prep. SMOKIN' GENIE (14) hasn't done anything to write home about to date, but this is the easiest race she's contested and she draws to advantage. WAYNE'S DREAM (10) also draws well and doesn't need to improve much on the two runs this campaign to feature. ACANTILADO (1) was outclassed in a handy maiden last time, so will this more to his liking. SHE'S OURVALENTINE (13) was beaten a long way last start but wasn't that far off second in a race won by one who looks well above average and she seemed to appreciate firmer footing that day.
